snippet.textDisplay:
My interpretation of the song:

Male Singer (Poet):
O Bulbuli (nightingale) in the garden!
On flower boughs, don't you swing today....
Even now the flower buds sleep in slumberous disarray.......

Even now on empty boughs, the north wind sway days and nights....
Not come yet.... the honey drunk bees who sing Ghazal with southern wind.... 

Oh when will the flower princess part her veil to reveal herself…..
The kiss of the dew will wake her, making her chick red.....

Female Singer (Bulbuli):
Swing, swing, I swing away 
But where does her (Flower bud) sleep break?
Spring has come calling..... wake now friend!
Surely, I will wake you from sleep... I remain awake in that hope....
Oh the south wind has arrived...the bees and birds are enamored in your love.. 
Wake, wake, wake now friend ... spring has come yonder...
The south wind is calling "Where is my beloved I wonder!!!"
